If `bind.cardview.isClickable` does not exist, it means that you're trying to access the `isClickable` property on a view that is not a `CardView`. The `isClickable` property is specific to the `CardView` class and is not available on other views.

To disable the click event on a `CardView`, you need to make sure that you have a reference to the `CardView` instance in your code. Here's an example of how you can do it in your adapter's `ViewHolder`:

```kotlin
class MyAdapter(private val data: List<DataItem>) : RecyclerView.Adapter<MyAdapter.ViewHolder>() {

    override fun onCreateViewHolder(parent: ViewGroup, viewType: Int): ViewHolder {
        val itemView = LayoutInflater.from(parent.context).inflate(R.layout.item_layout, parent, false)
        return ViewHolder(itemView)
    }

    override fun onBindViewHolder(holder: ViewHolder, position: Int) {
        val item = data[position]
        holder.bind(item)

        // Disable click on the CardView
        holder.cardView.isClickable = false
        holder.cardView.isFocusable = false
    }

    inner class ViewHolder(itemView: View) : RecyclerView.ViewHolder(itemView) {
        val cardView: CardView = itemView.findViewById(R.id.myCardView)

        fun bind(item: DataItem) {
            // Bind your data to the views
        }
    }
}
```

In this example, we're assuming that your `item_layout.xml` file contains a `CardView` with the ID `myCardView`. In the `ViewHolder` class, we're finding the `CardView` instance using `findViewById(R.id.myCardView)` and storing it in the `cardView` property.

Then, in the `onBindViewHolder` method, we can access the `CardView` instance using `holder.cardView` and set the `isClickable` and `isFocusable` properties to `false`.

Make sure that you have the correct ID for your `CardView` in the layout file and that you're using the correct ID when finding the view in your `ViewHolder` class.

If you're not using a `RecyclerView` and have a direct reference to the `CardView` instance, you can disable the click event directly on that instance:

```kotlin
val myCardView: CardView = findViewById(R.id.myCardView)
myCardView.isClickable = false
myCardView.isFocusable = false
```

By setting `isClickable` and `isFocusable` to `false`, you'll prevent the `CardView` from receiving click events and becoming focused, effectively disabling the click event on the `CardView`.

