```

3. Alternatively, you can use Build Configurations or Flavors to define different values for the `BASE_URL` constant and access it directly in your code without importing separate classes.

In your `build.gradle` file, you can define different values for `BASE_URL` in the `buildTypes` or `productFlavors` blocks:

```gradle
android {
    defaultConfig {
        buildConfigField "String", "BASE_URL", "\"https://serviceonline.elisonline.co.uk/SolMaster/Ordering.wso/\""
    }

    productFlavors {
        development {
            buildConfigField "String", "BASE_URL", "\"http://serviceonlinetest.elisonline.co.uk/SolMasterTraining5/ordering.wso/\""
        }
        production {
            // Use the default value from defaultConfig
        }
    }
}
```

Then, in your code, you can access the `BASE_URL` value using `BuildConfig.BASE_URL`.

```kotlin
