            else -> handleUnknownError()
        }
    }
}
```

In this modified code, we're using `when (val apiResponse = response)` to capture the value of `response` in a new variable `apiResponse`. This way, the compiler can infer the possible types of `apiResponse` based on the `when` branches, and it should no longer complain about unreachable branches.

