If the `sendOrderToSOL` function in the `ArticleEntryCardFragment` is getting a null response even when there is a successful response, it could be due to an issue with the way the `ApiResponse` is being handled in the `ArticleEntryViewModel`.

In the `handleSendOrderResponse` function of the `ArticleEntryViewModel`, you're returning an instance of `ApiResponse.Success` with the `response.body()` as the data. However, if the `response.body()` is null, the `ApiResponse.Success` instance will have a null `data` property.

Here's how you can modify the `handleSendOrderResponse` function to handle the case where `response.body()` is null:

```kotlin
private fun handleSendOrderResponse(response: Response<OrderEventResponse>): ApiResponse<OrderEventResponse> {
    return when {
        response.isSuccessful && response.body()?.success == true && response.body()?.messages?.isEmpty() == true -> {
            response.body()?.let {
                ApiResponse.Success(it)
            } ?: ApiResponse.UnknownError("Unknown error occurred")
        }
        response.isSuccessful && response.body()?.messages?.any { it.contains(DATE_TOO_LATE, ignoreCase = true) } == true -> {
            ApiResponse.ErrorSendOrderDate(response.body()?.messages.toString())
        }
        response.isSuccessful && response.body()?.messages?.none { it.contains(DATE_TOO_LATE, ignoreCase = true) } == true -> {
            ApiResponse.Error(response.body()?.messages.toString())
        }
        !response.isSuccessful && response.code() == 401 -> {
            ApiResponse.ErrorLogin("Authentication failed")
        }
        !response.isSuccessful && response.body()?.messages?.isNotEmpty() == true -> {
            ApiResponse.Error(response.body()?.messages.toString())
        }
        else -> {
            ApiResponse.UnknownError("Unknown error occurred")
        }
    }
}
```

In this modified `handleSendOrderResponse` function, we're using the `let` function to handle the case where `response.body()` is null. If `response.body()` is not null, we create an instance of `ApiResponse.Success` with the non-null `response.body()`. If `response.body()` is null, we create an instance of `ApiResponse.UnknownError` with the message "Unknown error occurred".

With this modification, if the server returns a successful response with a null `body`, the `sendOrderToSOL` function in the `ArticleEntryCardFragment` will receive an `ApiResponse.UnknownError` instead of a null response.

