To set a navigation for the `R.id.home_button` menu item, you can modify the `navControllerListener` implementation in the `MainActivity.kt` file. Here's an example of how you could do it:

```kotlin
private val navControllerListener = NavController.OnDestinationChangedListener { _, destination, _ ->
    when (destination.id) {
        R.id.loginFragment -> showHideToolbar(false)
        R.id.landingPageFragment -> showHideToolbar(false)
        R.id.home_button -> {
            // Navigate to the desired destination
            navController.navigate(R.id.your_destination_id)
        }
        else -> showHideToolbar(true)
    }
}
```

In this example, when the destination ID is `R.id.home_button`, you can navigate to the desired destination by calling `navController.navigate(R.id.your_destination_id)`, where `R.id.your_destination_id` is the ID of the destination you want to navigate to.

