Based on the provided codebase context, specifically the `LoginFragment.kt` file, you can make each build variant get the correct remote config from Firebase by using different keys for each build variant in the `fireBaseRemoteConfig()` function.

Here's how you can modify the `fireBaseRemoteConfig()` function to achieve this:

```kotlin
private fun fireBaseRemoteConfig() {
    // sets the Firebase Remote Config settings
    val remoteConfig: FirebaseRemoteConfig = Firebase.remoteConfig
    val configSettings = remoteConfigSettings {
        minimumFetchIntervalInSeconds = 3600
    }
    remoteConfig.setConfigSettingsAsync(configSettings)
    remoteConfig.setDefaultsAsync(R.xml.remote_config_defaults_orig)
    // Fetches remote config parameters setup in the Firebase console.
    remoteConfig.fetchAndActivate().addOnCompleteListener { task ->
        if (task.isSuccessful) {
            when (sharedViewModel.flavor.value) {
                "development" -> {
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.loginURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_LoginURL_dev")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.logoutURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_LogoutURL_dev")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.orderInfoURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_OrderInfoURL_dev")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.orderEventURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_OrderEventURL_dev")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.serviceCheckURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_ServiceCheckURL_dev")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.mainURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_MainURL_dev")
                }
                "production" -> {
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.loginURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_LoginURL_prod")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.logoutURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_LogoutURL_prod")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.orderInfoURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_OrderInfoURL_prod")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.orderEventURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_OrderEventURL_prod")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.serviceCheckURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_ServiceCheckURL_prod")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.mainURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_MainURL_prod")
                }
                "staging" -> {
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.loginURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_LoginURL_staging")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.logoutURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_LogoutURL_staging")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.orderInfoURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_OrderInfoURL_staging")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.orderEventURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_OrderEventURL_staging")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.serviceCheckURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_ServiceCheckURL_staging")
                    FirebaseRemoteConfigValues.mainURL =
                        remoteConfig.getString("SOLStock_MainURL_staging")
                }
            }
        } else {
            // Handle the case when the fetch fails
            // You can use default values or handle the error as needed
        }
    }
}
```

In this modified version of the `fireBaseRemoteConfig()` function, we're using a `when` statement to check the value of `sharedViewModel.flavor.value`, which represents the current build variant (development, production, or staging).

Based on the build variant, we're using different keys to retrieve the corresponding remote config values from Firebase. For example, for the "development" build variant, we're using keys like `SOLStock_LoginURL_dev`, `SOLStock_LogoutURL_dev`, etc.

Make sure to set the appropriate remote config values in the Firebase console for each build variant, using the corresponding keys (e.g., `SOLStock_LoginURL_dev`, `SOLStock_LoginURL_prod`, `SOLStock_LoginURL_staging`).

By using this approach, each build variant will fetch and use the correct remote config values from Firebase based on the keys specific to that variant.

Note: You'll need to replace the placeholders (`SOLStock_LoginURL_dev`, `SOLStock_LoginURL_prod`, `SOLStock_LoginURL_staging`, etc.) with the actual keys you've set in the Firebase Remote Config console for each build variant.

