By using `viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch`, you don't need to manually cancel the coroutine in the `onDestroyView` method, as it will be automatically canceled when the Fragment's view is destroyed. However, I've kept the `internetCheckJob?.cancel()` line in the `onDestroyView` method as an extra precaution.

